The line of thought is that `ind_hyp` provides a simplification for `List.foldl afunc [] tail`. We can use `simp only [ind_hyp]` to apply this. This will transform the goal. If the antecedent `(¬∃ location ∈ head :: tail, location.2 = index₁)` holds, then `ind_hyp` tells us that `List.foldl afunc [] tail = []`. So the goal becomes `(¬∃ location ∈ head, location.2 = index₁) → True`.

