This `simp` tactic will use the equivalence `h5` to simplify `h_exists`. If `h_exists` is `∃ location ∈ allChildren, location.2 = index₁`, then `simp [h5]` will turn it into `¬(List.foldl afunc [] allChildren = [])`. This is then used in the contradiction proof for the forward direction.

